<zk>
	<vlayout>
		<label value="ZK-5992 — tbeditor library-property baseline"/>
		<label multiline="true">
What this page shows: a bare tbeditor with NO plugins= attribute, used to verify
the application-wide library property and the pluginPath override.

How to verify (browser developer tools → Network):
1. With no library property set: the editor requests NO plugin assets.
2. Set library-property org.zkoss.zkmax.zul.tbeditor.plugins = "table" (in zk.xml), reload:
   this editor now loads trumbowyg.table.js app-wide, with no per-component change.
3. Set library-property org.zkoss.zkmax.zul.tbeditor.pluginPath to a custom prefix, reload:
   plugin assets are requested from that prefix instead of the bundled ~./js/.../ext/plugins/.
		</label>
		<tbeditor id="tb" width="500px"/>
	</vlayout>
</zk>
